message.content: cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.NEURON - This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with automated image segmentation techniques. It may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories as it uses Deep Convolutional Neural Networks (DCNN) segmentation methods. Additionally, it may belong to the Medical Imaging (cs.MED) category as it deals with MRI scans and the detection of splenomegaly. Finally, it may also belong to the Neurons and Cognition (cs.NEURON) category as it uses a Markovian discriminator to alleviate false positives.
